Description:
A fabulous Find - Approx 3.3 Acres
A very appealing small acreage situated just off the Bass Hwy in a secluded setting with a superb Rural vista with distant bay views on approx 3.3 acres. Rural fencing to 3 sides, electricity, mains water and telephone available to the property. Ideal to establish your dream hobby farm with heaps of room for the caravan, boat & cars. Space for children to run around and play. Short distance to the Bass Valley Primary School. Only a short drive to the jetty, boat ramp & beach. Come and enjoy the beauty of the Bass coast region.

Description:
ABSOLUTE FORESHORE STUNNER
Rarely can you find such an attractive property set right on the foreshore, with magical views of Western Port Bay to both French Island and Phillip Island. Well here it is, ready to make your very own. Renovated with flair and an eye for detail the home has beautifully polished timber floors and open plan living, split system air conditioner, timber Venetians, a well- appointed kitchen, stainless steel stove and dishwasher. The home opens to a large enclosed entertaining deck with child proof gate, beautiful bay views and direct access to the beach. The master bedroom suite has a private balcony, with views to the water, walk in robe and en-suite. There are two bedrooms downstairs with a shared family bathroom with separate toilet and laundry. Outside is a fully fenced yard, carport and two sheds.
This is an opportunity to purchase a wonderfully presented, low maintenance beach escape in a quiet location - right on the beach where you can watch the sunset sitting either on the deck or the bench seat on the foreshore with a glass of wine and enjoy the peace and tranquil ambiance.
Within walking distance to the shops, doctors, public transport and services that Grantville has to offer, only a few minutes to wineries and 20 minutes to Phillip Island, 30 minutes to Cranbourne, 35 minutes to Pakenham. Your opportunity to own a piece of foreshore is here!

Description:
Room for a growing family – 1100m2 block
Set on a generous 1100m2 block, this home is peacefully located in one of Lang Lang’s prized pockets of real estate. This home has been fully renovated and offers spacious open plan living with 4 bedrooms, master with ENS and WIR, two large living areas and a modern kitchen. The living room opens onto a large undercover area that is perfect for entertaining. Some of the many features include:
- Modern kitchen with quality fittings & appliances
- 12 volt roller shutters on north facing windows
- Large 8kw split system for heating and cooling
- 6mt x 3mt shed with power & concrete floor
Close to the local primary school and positioned for living convenience, it is in a ‘walk to everything’ location and perfectly suited for a growing family. Too many features to mention so an inspection is a must.

FORSHORE IMMACULATE BARGAIN HOME
With the foreshore on your doorstep, this perfectly presented property won’t last long, have you been dreaming of living on the foreshore but thought it was out of your reach financially, well make your dream come true. This great property situated on a quiet no through road Malcolm Drive foreshore grants you that lifestyle and you will feel right at home in such comfortable surroundings.
Beautifully presented gardens and views that offer you and the family outdoor entertaining.
The home offers open plan living, three bedrooms galley style kitchen & bathroom.
Down stairs there’s a large laundry that has its own laundry Shute.
A leisurely stroll along the beachfront provides breathtaking views of French Island while the home itself is located only minutes from the Grantville shopping precinct which has all your needs accommodated. The region is rich with places to explore including the award winning Bass River Winery, Bassine Specialty Cheeses, local farmers markets and, of course, all there is to see and do in Phillip Island and along the popular Bass Coast. You will need to act quickly to secure this opportunity.
Agent available 7 days a week.

Description:
12 ACRE HOBBY FARM
Get away from it all to relax and enjoy....
This generous hardy plank home has a large formal living area complete with wood fire heater, three large bedrooms all with built in robes a full ensuite to the master and a study area is complimented by a stunning sun room providing a wonderful second living space to enjoy, aircon and ceiling fan in place.
The kitchen has been renovated to a high standard providing loads of cupboard space and includes European appliances, a smeg induction cook top with wok. The home is freshly painted throughout. The back veranda has a sheltered bbq area for entertaining family and friends.
The property has a large range of shedding in various locations suitable for storing feed or as horse shelters, greenhouse and chook pen, expansive 4 car garage plus machinery shed with wash basin, w/c and kitchenette, light and power.
Running from Albert Road to the foreshore and ideal as a hobby farm for horses, dogs, sheep, cattle or fishermen, no near neighbours and it's set within close proximity to Grantville, fifteen minutes to Philip Island, just over an hour to CBD.
This property screams opportunity so make that call today!!!!!!

Description:
PRESTIGIOUS 3 LEVEL HOME BY THE BAY
FOR SALE - This attractive home is set in one of the most sought after locations in the area, picturesque and quiet and only a very short walk to the foreshore, on a large 869m2 block with plenty of space to park cars, boats or caravans. The home itself boast three levels, having a spacious entry, laundry and linen cupboards then up the the second level where you will discover three spacious bedrooms, the master has a walk-in robe and full ensuite, a family bathroom with a bath and separate shower, a second living area or rumpus room with polished floors and is light and bright with a split system air conditioner and sliding doors leading to one of the balconies and lovely bay views . The third level has a study area and opens out to a delightful large open plan family and dining area with polished timber floors and a modern and spacious kitchen to one side with stainless steel appliances and dishwasher. There is also another reverse cycle air conditioner on this level and sliding doors leading to a larger deck with impressive bay views. Outside is an large undercover carport area, minimal gardens, large block and fully fenced with two entries. You can enjoy the beautiful coastal walks and walking track close by, boat ramp, community center, playground, bowls, tennis courts, local shop and v-line bus only a few minutes away. Approx 20 minutes to Phillip Island. This is a must see property. Agent available 7 days a week.

Description:
Enjoy the Sunsets over Westernport
A fabulous level lot of 555m2 is titled and ready for you to build your home on Eastern Shores Estate, Grantville. Offering a frontage of 17 metres and depth of 32.60 metres, the house design options are endless. You can put the car away as the land is only minutes walking distance to everything including the beach, boat ramp, shops and post office.
Located at the gateway to the beautiful Bass Coast, Eastern Shores Estate is a comfortable 80 minute drive from Melbourne metropolitan and a 40 minute commute to the South Eastern suburbs of Dandenong and Pakenham.
Within close proximity to the local wineries, the surf beaches at Philip Island, Kilcunda and Inverloch and the boating/fishing and national parks you will enjoy great day trips along the coast.

Description:
BAY & RURAL VIEWS !!!!
Bayview Avenue is a unique location being a no through road to waterfront with native treed surrounds. On offer is this 5 year old modern home with spacious living and kitchen area, tiled floors throughout except for bedrooms, split-system air conditioner, sliding door from living to covered outdoor deck area, perfect for entertaining and just soaking up the bay views and tranquillity. There are 3 good size bedrooms all with wall to wall carpet, and built in robes, master with walk-in, ensuite, family bathroom has full bath and separate shower and good size laundry. The home has a charming feel as soon as you walk through
the front door. The backyard is fenced and has plenty of space, 2 garden
sheds and gorgeous established gardens. Close by is a 24 hour boat ramp, shop, primary school, kindergarten and bus stop. A major shopping centre is approx.. 25 mins and Phillip Island. The property is currently tenanted at $300 per week for 12 months.

Description:
Cosy Cottage On 1/4 Acre
This warm feel, 3 bedroom home on 1,000m2 block. New carpets and home has been painted inside and out. Open plan living, wood heater and split system air conditioner. Slate flooring throughout wet areas in family, kitchen and hallway. Master bedroom has Walk in robe, ensuite and ceiling fan. Kitchen has been fitted with a new stove and Dishlex dishwasher, which is only 2 years old. 2 door pantry and plenty of bench space. 2nd bathroom has a bath, shower and vanity.
Front of house features a bull nose verandah with new spotted gum timber deck and ramp. A long wide concrete drive leading to backyard and 2 car garage with power and concrete, carport & wood shed. Pergola under roof line with pavers. Neat gardens, picket fence and walking distance to school. Room for boat, caravan etc.

Description:
Your New lifestyle awaits you!
Located in the sleepy seaside Village of Pioneer Bay is this beautifully renovated 3 bedroom home offering you more than just a home but a new lifestyle! There is nothing to do in this home except bring you belongings and move in.
As you enter the home it opens to a large entrance hall which leads through to a huge living, kitchen and meals area, the recently updated kitchen comes complete with 900mm stainless steel cooker, dishwasher, loads of cupboard space and caeserstone benches.
The master suite is located at the rear of the home away from the other bedrooms allowing for privacy and is complete with a fully fitted walk-in robe and direct access to the bathroom and separate Wc. The other 2 bedrooms are to the front of the home and are of good size.
Car accommodation has been covered with a single carport under the roof line of the home and a free standing double garage to the rear of the block complete with concrete, power, remote and shelving with a further 2 garden sheds to allow for more storage. Next to the double garage there is enough space to store your boat or even a caravan.

Description:
50 ACRES OF PURE SERENITY
Your opportunity to create your own private bush sanctuary is here, right on the gateway to Phillip Island yet less than an hour's drive to the sparkling lights of Melbourne. Complete with a current planning and building permit and approved plans, properties such as this are becoming increasingly difficult to find.
Approximately 50 acres of quality land largely occupied by numerous varieties of flourishing gums is home to many species of Australian fauna. Kangaroos, wallabies, echidnas, goannas and spectacular soaring eagles overhead are some of the animals you will find.
A brand new quality built 3 bay Colourbond shed measuring 15m x 9.6m is situated nearby your new home site and has plenty of room for all of your toys! There is also further shedding at the rear of the property where magnificent mountainous views are sure to take your eye.
It doesn't get any better than this! Stop dreaming and start living the dream. Call today for further information or to organise your tour of this extremely special property.

Description:
Peaceful Oasis Retreat with Beautiful Bay views
Imagine watching the beautiful sunrise over the bay from your garden. Sounds attractive then yes this property could be for you. This is a wonderful opportunity to acquire a lovely bay side property in the quiet sleepy hollow of Tenby Point. This property is set on a gently elevated block of approx 1/3 acre and offers a 60 foot approx frontage with lane access to the rear. There is a comfortable 2 bedroom cottage that offers some lovely features including a well appointed kitchen & bathroom, split system air conditioning and wood fire plus so much more. There is even a caravan that can stay for extra accommodation for the drop in visitors or the in-laws. There is a big double garage & workshop and the property is serviced by mains water, ground water bore and tank water (you'll never go thirsty). Be quick for this as vendor has priced the property to sell!
